data.chText: 做得过分；做得过火；夸张
data.enText: to do sth too much; to exaggerate sth
She really overdid the sympathy (= and so did not seem sincere) .
to use too much of sth
Don't overdo the salt in the food.

data.chText: 要适当地使用插图，但不宜过多。
data.enText: Use illustrations where appropriate but don't overdo it .
to cook sth for too long

data.chText: 这鱼烧的时间太长，都干掉了。
data.enText: The fish was overdone and very dry.
to work, study, etc. too hard or for too long

data.chText: 我在健身房练得过火了，结果弄伤了背。
data.enText: I overdid it in the gym and hurt my back.
to work, study, etc. too hard or for too long

data.chText: 我在健身房练得过火了，结果弄伤了背。
data.enText: I overdid it in the gym and hurt my back.

tr: do something to an excessive degree
example: He overdid it last night when he did 100 pushups

value.def: If someone overdoes something, they behave in an exaggerated or extreme way.

example.ex: ...a recognition by the US central bank that it may have overdone its tightening when it pushed rates up to 6 per cent...
example.tran: 美国中央银行承认将利率上调至6%可能是过度紧缩了银根

example.ex: He wants to give up working and stay home to look after the children. She feels, however, that this is overdoing it a bit.
example.tran: 他想辞去工作，在家照看孩子。而她却觉得这样做有些过头。

value.tran: 把…做得过分；把…做得过火；对…过于夸张

value.def: If you overdo an activity, you try to do more than you can physically manage.

example.ex: It is important never to overdo new exercises...
example.tran: 重要的是,不要过度练习新学的动作。

example.ex: The taxi drivers' association is urging its members, who can work as many hours as they want, not to overdo it.
example.tran: 出租车司机协会劝告那些工作时长不受限制的会员不要疲劳驾驶。
